et telus mobility telus tv subsidiaries public mobile koodo mobile website wwwteluscom telus corporation stylized as telus is a canadian national telecommunications company that provides a wide range of telecommunications products and services including internet access voice entertainment healthcare video and iptv television the company is based in the vancouver british columbia area it was originally based in edmonton alberta before its merger with bctel in  teluss wireless division telus mobility offers hspa and ltebased mobile phone networks telus is the incumbent local exchange carrier in british columbia and alberta teluss primary competitors are shaw communications in the western provinces and bell canada and vidéotron general partnership in quebec telus is a member of the british columbia technology industry association contents  history  labour dispute  telus international  relaunch of clearnet  nonvoting share conversion  purchase of public mobile  reception  marketing strategies   christmas campaign  sponsorship  see also  references  external links historyedit telus in markville shopping centre telus at hillcrest mall telus building the boot in burnaby british columbia telus company was formed in  by the government of alberta as telus communications a holding company in order to facilitate the privatization of a crown corporation the alberta government telephones commission agt in  it acquired edmonton telephones corporation ed tel from the city of edmonton making telus the sole provider of telephone service a in alberta in  telus was introduced to the public as the consumer brand replacing both agt and edtel in  telus and bctel announced a proposed merger the merger was completed in  with the corporate name slightly modified to telus corporation while the merged company chose to retain the telus name it moved its headquarters from edmonton to vancouver the merger created canadas second largest telcom with  of market share compared to bell canadas  large swaths of rural quebec mainly the gaspé peninsula and the north shore were served from  by an entity known as corporation de téléphone et de pouvoir de québec and in  this became known as québec téléphone in  the anglocanadian telephone company a subsidiary of general telephone and electronics of stamford connecticut later gte became a majority shareholder in québec téléphone anglocanadian also owned bctel and gte later merged into verizon also owned services in barbados dominican republic jamaica and trinidad and tobago in  groupe québectel was established to own québec téléphone following the merger of bctel with telus of alberta gte sold its interests in québec téléphone to telus in august  which renamed it telus québec on april   in late  american telecom verizon communications sold its  stake in telus this was so that verizon could focus more on its own services labour disputeedit after the telusbctel merger unionized employees voted to certify the telecommunications workers union twu as the sole bargaining agent for the expanded companys workforce the twu had previously been the union representing bctel employees  it replaced the international brotherhood of electrical workers ibew in alberta a labour dispute between telus and the twu began after the previous contract negotiated with bctel before the telus merger expired at the end of  after telus made its final offer to the twu it informed the union of its intention to bring an end to the dispute by unilaterally implementing its april  offer to employees in alberta and british columbia the next day the union went on strike although as is common in disputes where an employer attempts to unilaterally implement a new contract the union consistently referred to the dispute as a lockout on july   telus blocked its internet subscribers from accessing a website supporting striking union members the company expressed concerns over content on the site saying it identified employees crossing picket lines and encouraged disruptive behaviour while the union alleged it amounted to censorship the british columbia civil liberties association issued an official objection to the unilateral blocking on july  stating telus is leveraging its power as a telecommunications service provider to censor a specific group shut down debate and limit the messages conveyed about the current labour dispute an alberta court injunction ordered the blocked website voices for change to remove postings of telus employee photos and other intimidating or threatening material the site owner agreed to comply and telus unblocked the website telus and the twu ratified a tentative agreement on november   ending the dispute telus internationaledit telus international is telus’ global arm providing global contact center and business process outsourcing services to corporations in the financial services consumer electronics and gaming telecommunications energy and utilities industries telus international has contact centers in the philippines the united kingdom central america guatemala and el salvador and eastern europe bulgaria and romania where it is known as telus international europe relaunch of clearnetedit main article clearnet telus mobility in april  telus mobility relaunched the clearnet brand as a limited market trial in kelowna british columbia and red deer alberta the company again closed to new business in june  nonvoting share conversionedit in february  telus exchanged all nonvoting shares into common shares on a oneforone basis purchase of public mobileedit main article public mobile in october  telus acquired minor mobile phone provider public mobile and relaunched it in  as a value brand mvno on the telus network receptionedit in october  telus was named one of british columbias top employers by mediacorp canada inc which was announced by the vancouver sun the province and the victoria timescolonist in recent years the company has been accused of taking actions to hinder the emergence of competition in canadian telecommunications this along with other industry concerns has led to consumer and industry pressure to reform the regulatory system governing the canadian telecommunications industry marketing strategiesedit this section contains wording that promotes the subject in a subjective manner without imparting real information please remove or replace such wording and instead of making proclamations about a subjects importance use facts and attribution to demonstrate that importance february  learn how and when to remove this template message a telus store in moncton new brunswick  christmas campaignedit for the christmas season in  an ad campaign was launched involving a hippopotamus named hazina from the greater vancouver zoo accompanied by the song i want a hippopotamus for christmas on may   the zoo was formally charged with animal cruelty for their treatment of hazina telus spokesman shawn hall said telus was aware that concerns had been raised around hazinas living conditions which is why it stipulated that the  it paid the zoo for using hazina go directly toward building a new enclosure for her sponsorshipedit telus sponsors the calgary science centre science world in vancouver and the odyssium in edmonton both vancouver and edmonton science museums were subsequently renamed as telus world of science and calgary was renamed to telus spark telus funds the annual kokanee crankworx freeride mountain bike and world ski  snowboard festivals both held in whistler british columbia telus was a sponsor and marketing partner of hockey canada since  and the title sponsor of canadas national midget hockey championship the telus cup since  telus has been a sponsor of rogers sportsnets regional broadcasts of calgary flames and edmonton oilers games telus is active in canadian professional golf as title sponsor of the telus open and the telus skins game telus is the namesake tenant in several office buildings including the telus convention centre in calgary tour telus in montreal telus plaza in edmonton and telus house in toronto beginning in  telus began sponsoring canadas largest nationwide technology education event the html see alsoedit companies portal clearnet communications cybertipca koodo mobile list of canadian mobile phone companies mike cellular network telus tv referencesedit  telus  google search googleca   a b c about telus company history telus corporate website retrieved february    wilson kevin g deregulating telecommunications us and canadian telecommunications  rowman  littlefield  isbn  page   alberta online encyclopedia alberta government telephones albertas telephone heritage  crtc letter dated june   retrieved february   archived april   at the wayback machine  feakins kathryn h the telus story brand management strategies for a customerfocused identity pdf retrieved february     telus company history retrieved    a b hunter jennifer bc telecomtelus merger macleans magazine november    canadas second largest telecommunications firm selects clicklearn for learning initiative targeting  employees business wire november    fact sheet – telus and the companys rob placing telus corporate site retrieved february    verizon sells stake in canadas telus techdirtcom retrieved december    a b telus cuts subscriber access to prounion website cbc news july    doctorow cory phone company blocks access to telecoms unions website boingboing july    bccla denounces blocking of website by telus archived  at the wayback machine bc civil liberties association press release july    alberta court grants interim injunction against posting telus employee photos telus media release july     of telus workers say no to continued labour action telecommunications industry news november    trichur rita  january  telus shareconversion plan underway retrieved  may    hardy ian  october  telus to acquire  of public mobile mobile syrup retrieved  november    hardy ian telus rebrands public mobile as canada’s cooperative wireless provid