which were acquired in  the it department for telus corporation is dispersed across several locations in canada core department leadership is located at the company’s headquarters in burnaby bc a location in longueuil qc serves as the headquarters for telus health telus mobility staff… morethe it department for telus corporation is dispersed across several locations in canada core department leadership is located at the company’s headquarters in burnaby bc a location in longueuil qc serves as the headquarters for telus health telus mobility staff members are mainly located in scarborough on other smaller sites support specialized or regional operations and house fewer technical assets telus’ it staff members are divided between internal operations and clientfacing functions leaders working in technology strategy oversee the resources and staff that manage the various clientfacing technology operations staff working in this area primarily have responsibilities in business intelligence and service delivery internally the company has staff dedicated to maintaining networks and infrastructure business support operations data centers and information security telus has embraced cloud technologies throughout its corporate operations in  the company began to host some of its application platforms online since then the company has continued to use the cloud to meet storage demands and support large databases for big data initiatives in  telus began work on a new data center to support cloud operations internally as well as provide cloud services to consumers the company cloud strategy was further supported by the acquisitions of wolf medical systems and kinlogix  these acquisitions support telus health’s push into cloudbased medical record services the it budget is typically finalized in q it intelligence snippets  • pb data volume companywide across  data centers and expects an annual data growth of  • of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of  •corporate it manages  mobile devices while  are managed elsewhere •corporate it manages  desktops •cost is the primary consideration for buying hardware and its standardized on  product vendors •data center strategy is centered on virtualizing x servers for most applications standalone servers or mainframes for business critical applications standardizing on unified server storage and network stacks and minimizing cost •long term plan for running new applications is to add servers and virtualize but no new facilities are scheduled sector industry technology telecommunications services employees  revenue b fye  breaking news on investment signals date type inside scoop  pain point topic applications company telus corporation vancouver bc opportunity a front line source has indicated that the organization is experiencing pain related to the qualityreliability of its application development process the organization is likely to spend to address this issue live on  update we are exploring methodologies to address this issue  project scoop topic data warehousing company telus corporation vancouver bc opportunity a frontline source has indicated that data warehouse solutions are a spending priority the organization has selected fujitsu enterprise solutions and is currently implementing this initiative will take place companywide the organization uses contingentcontract workers for technology initiatives live on  update we are now selecting vendors  pain point topic applications company telus corporation vancouver bc opportunity a front line source has indicated that the organization is experiencing pain related to the complexity of enterprise application portfolios live on  update we are creating a new team to address this issue want full access to this profile and more rainkings clients have access to over  new investment signals published daily which provide insights on spending initiatives pain points management changes and more from companies around the globe interested in becoming a cl